By Teniola Ibitola Lagos – Four men, Tochukwu Chukwuka, Ebere Okoro, Emmanuel Okorie and Matthew Durosimi, on Tuesday, appeared before an Ebute Meta Magistrates’ Court, Lagos for allegedly theft of a tricycle, Chukwuka, 38, Okoro, 42; Okorie, 34; and Durosimi, 19, are to face trial on a two count charge of conspiracy and stealing but the defendants pleaded not guilty to the charges. Earlier, the prosecutor, Insp Kehinde Omisakin, had told the court that the defendants committed the offences in April at No. 4, Wasiu Wasiri at the back of Little Base School, Iba town. The prosecutor alleged that the defendants had stolen a tricycle marked SMK 346 QF, valued N750,000 belonging to Chibike Ofoegbu. According to her, the offences contravene Sections 287 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The chief magistrate, Mrs A.O. Komolafe, granted the first defendant bail in the sum of N200,000 while the other three defendants were granted bail in the sum of N100,000 with two sureties each in like sum. The court adjourned the case until July 9 for mention.